I saw Coln Colonel
Yoakum, and Mr Mister Harrison, they speak highly creditable of you boys, and of the whole company in their ready willingness to purform perform their duties, It is generally understood from various sources that it stand in higher estimation for its military pride, good order and disciplin discipline than any company in service; this is truly gratifying to the citizens of your county, they speak of it boastingly, I think you soaldiers soldiers should prise prize and honour & hold your officers in high estimation for their good order attention to good order, strict disciplin & military pride; without; the best of soaldiers would be degraded,_ I under stand from Coln Colonel
Yocum Yoakum it is proberbly probable that it will be the last of this month before his regiment will be discharged, I would rather you all had three months longar longer to stay under strict disciplin that you might become better acquainted with military duties, in camp__ Mr Harrison, says you wanted me to meet you with a horse when you started home;
